Iconic R&B group Boys II Men was scheduled to perform in South Africa in April 2020. JOHANNESBURG - The spread of the coronavirus (COVID-19) has led to the cancellation or the postponement of some of the biggest events around the world. TV productions with live audiences, sporting events, social gatherings, and concerts have had to be delayed as the number of infected people increases. SUMMARY: Ramaphosa announces COVID-19 controls On Sunday, President Cyril Ramaphosa announced measures Cabinet has decided to implement to reduce the impact of the virus. One of those measures include the prohibition of gatherings of more than 100 people. Several local events have been postponed since the outbreak and ticket-holders are encouraged to visit the respective websites regarding the refund of tickets. Below is a list of some of the events that have been postponed: Cape Town International Jazz Festival Boys II Men and Scorpion Kings Live concerts MTN Bushfire AfrikaBurn